		<tr>
			<td class="BoardRowB" colspan=3>
				Baking is EASY (for the Fed up Dark Elf) <br>  <br> First of all... <br> I was a master baker BEFORE I had spit <br> You can go from (1-80s) with Fish Fillets <br> (Fish + Jug of Sauces) <br> You can go from (80s-130s) with Fish Rolls <br> (Fish + Bat Wing) <br> There is a vendor in Neriak Commons, next to a fountain that sells unlimited fish <br> There is a vendor next to the bank that sells <br> unlimited Jug of Sauces <br> There is a vendor in East Commons, in a building near the inn CLOSEST to West Commons, she is a wierd NPC and is Indiff to everyone, I as a DE Necro could buy from her <br>  <br> The spit: <br> To get the spit you MUST buy it from a the vendor in East Commons, at the Trader's Emporium (something like that).  Now you have a few choices on how to get the spit. <br>  <br> 1. Ask a Light Race to get it for you <br> 2. Make an Enchanter Mule <br> 3. Pay an Enchanter to get it for you <br> 4. Do it yourself (the hard way) <br>  <br> ((SPOILER)) <br> As a Dark Elf you are NOT KoS to most to the Guards or most NPCs in EAST Freeport and WEST Freeport.  The reality is that these zones are controled by the Corrupt Militia, which is controled by the Necromancer's, Shadow Knight's and Rogue's Guild.   <br>  <br> You have a starting faction with the Merchant NPC's of Dubious, but this faction goes up very quickly.  To raise your faction you must complete two newbie rogue quests, around 12 times.  The rogue's guild is in East Freeport, you can get there either via sewers or from under the dock, in a building thru a hidden door.   <br>  <br> The two NPC's you are looking for in the Rogue's Guild are Nestral (a DE), and Harkin (a Dwarf).  They will both give you notes, which you give to these two rogues in West Freeport, in the Thearte of Tranquility. (Janam, and Rebby)  They will then give you more stuff to take back to Nestral and Harkin.  Once you get back you just repeat the quests over and over.  Doing a full loop counts as ONE.  you must do 12 of these to be able to shop...It will take time as a SK, but should take more then an hour or two.  I personally did this quest a lot...I con Kindly with the Merchants, and Indifferent with the Guards, and Warmly with the Rogues Guild.  Note the guard faction will go up much slower. <br>  <br> Note only will this allow you to buy your spit, but also you can now buy Skewers and Scalers..a critical part of becoming a master Smith <br>  <br> Relcan <br> Dark Elf Necromancer <br> of the 29th Rotting Corpse <br> Rallos Zek <br>  <br> Master Brewer <br> Master Baker <br> Master Smithy <br> Master Potter <br> Master Fletcher <br> Excellent Tailor <br>    <br> 		

